Maintainer: Gülser Doğan Türkçelik <gulser.dogan@fetp.gov.tr>
Description: A comprehensive outbreak analysis toolkit for jamovi developed
    for Field Epidemiology Training Programme (FETP) practitioners. Provides
    standardised tools for: (1) automated linelist data quality assessment
    including duplicate detection, impossible dates, out-of-range values and
    inconsistent coding; (2) descriptive epidemiology with Person-Place-Time
    frequency tables, attack rates and 95% confidence intervals using Wilson
    (1927) score method; (3) epidemic curve generation with day/week/month
    aggregation; (4) cohort study analysis with Risk Ratio and Attributable
    Risk; (5) case-control study analysis with Odds Ratio; (6) Mantel-Haenszel
    stratified analysis with Breslow-Day test for effect modification; (7)
    multivariable logistic regression with automatic confounder screening; and
    (8) sample size calculators for cohort and case-control designs.
    Statistical methods follow Rothman & Greenland (2008) Modern Epidemiology,
    Schlesselman (1982), and CDC Field Epidemiology Manual guidelines.
